I thought you drew a carrot.

36
00:02:19,599 --> 00:02:21,720
Turns out it's a hole to hide.

37
00:02:22,239 --> 00:02:25,039
You'll develop an attachment
to the burrow after staying in it.

38
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:31,760
Turns out I was sad...

39
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:34,200
not because I like him a lot,

40
00:02:34,519 --> 00:02:35,720
but because...

41
00:02:35,879 --> 00:02:37,720
I lost the sense of security
he provided.

42
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:39,039
Sense of security?

43
00:02:41,239 --> 00:02:42,879
At least you had it.

44
00:02:44,319 --> 00:02:46,120
But, I didn't have it at all.

45
00:02:59,599 --> 00:03:01,000
What is this?

46
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:02,159
Don't look at this.

47
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:05,120
You allowed to draw but I can't look?

48
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,120
Zhou Shi?

49
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:17,399
So you like Zhou Shi?

50
00:03:19,039 --> 00:03:20,439
Stop staring at me.

51
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:23,159
Don't worry, I won't tell
your benefactor.

52
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:26,080
But, you'll have to make me happy.

53
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,280
To make a woman happy,

54
00:03:27,399 --> 00:03:29,399
the easiest way is to...

55
00:03:30,439 --> 00:03:31,640
swipe your card and buy a bag for me.

56
00:03:31,879 --> 00:03:33,159
Then, I'll keep your secret.

57
00:03:39,879 --> 00:03:40,879
I didn't bring it.

58
00:03:41,399 --> 00:03:43,080
Why don't you say you don't have money?

59
00:03:43,439 --> 00:03:44,560
Can you ask for something else?

60
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,039
If there is a way to make me happy...

61
00:03:46,039 --> 00:03:47,720
without spending money,

62
00:03:47,879 --> 00:03:49,480
I'll give you money, okay?

63
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,239
Okay.

64
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:52,760
What?

65
00:03:53,159 --> 00:03:54,239
Wait for me.

66
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,200
Where are you going?

67
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:00,439
Why is this person so mysterious?

68
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:12,282
[Take any you want for free]

69
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:14,879
You're giving them out for free?

70
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:26,439
Is this girl for free too?

71
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:30,119
I'm sorry, she's mine.

72
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:32,920
What are you doing?

73
00:04:35,599 --> 00:04:37,200
You're giving them out for free?

74
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,520
Yes.

75
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,599
Didn't you say they were useless?

76
00:04:40,719 --> 00:04:42,520
You're a wastrel! Put me down!

77
00:04:42,599 --> 00:04:42,999
No.

78
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:43,999
Are you putting me down?

79
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:44,640
No.

80
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:46,240
Put me down.

81
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:49,119
Put me down...

82
00:05:04,559 --> 00:05:05,680
What's going on?

83
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,640
Why did we kiss?

84
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,559
My heart is beating so fast.

85
00:05:11,439 --> 00:05:12,240
Just now...

86
00:05:12,400 --> 00:05:13,920
Why did you throw yourself on me?

87
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:15,960
Don't complain when you're in the wrong.

88
00:05:16,119 --> 00:05:17,480
You were moving around...

89
00:05:17,599 --> 00:05:18,719
and made me trip.

90
00:05:18,879 --> 00:05:19,839
Do you think I want to fall down?

91
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:20,640
You...

92
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,960
-Let me take a look.
-Don't touch me.

93
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:48,680
Nothing will happen if I take a look.

94
00:05:48,879 --> 00:05:50,080
I won't do anything to you.

95
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,319
If it's injured seriously,

96
00:05:51,439 --> 00:05:52,800
I can send you to the hospital.

97
00:06:00,279 --> 00:06:01,640
-Does it hurt?
-No.

98
00:06:01,999 --> 00:06:02,760
What about this?

99
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:04,760
Of course it hurts if you press it.

100
00:06:10,839 --> 00:06:11,999
It should be fine.

101
00:06:12,119 --> 00:06:13,159
Don't walk for the next few days.

102
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,839
Rest at home well.

103
00:06:15,039 --> 00:06:16,760
Don't walk? Are you joking?

104
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,279
If I don't walk, how can I go to school?

105
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,640
Not everyone is like you,

106
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,520
you have a driver to drive you anywhere.

107
00:06:21,760 --> 00:06:23,039
If you say yes,

108
00:06:23,159 --> 00:06:24,279
you can have a driver too.

109
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,159
Say yes to what?

110
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:29,599
Is it that hard to be my girlfriend?

111
00:06:30,559 --> 00:06:32,879
This isn't about saying yes or no.

112
00:06:33,879 --> 00:06:34,879
I get it.

113
00:06:35,279 --> 00:06:36,960
You have someone that you like.

114
00:06:37,159 --> 00:06:38,719
So, you can't say yes.

115
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:40,640
You know yet you're still asking?

116
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:43,480
To be frank, you don't have any hope...

117
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:45,879
for this relationship, right?

118
00:06:47,879 --> 00:06:48,960
Among all the flowers,

119
00:06:49,119 --> 00:06:51,800
you chose to take
the sea lavender and daisy.

120
00:06:52,039 --> 00:06:53,680
That means they are important to you.

121
00:06:56,879 --> 00:06:58,719
You even carved them...

122
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,360
on the letter.

123
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,960
It's really with you?

124
00:07:02,159 --> 00:07:04,319
That means that letter...

125
00:07:04,599 --> 00:07:05,839
I read it.

126
00:07:06,319 --> 00:07:07,960
Why did you read it?

127
00:07:09,719 --> 00:07:11,240
There are many types flowers
to confess love.

128
00:07:11,439 --> 00:07:13,839
But you chose
the sea lavender and daisy...

129
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:16,439
probably because they can either mean...

130
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:19,640
a long lasting secret love...

131
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:22,640
or a never ending friendship.

132
00:07:22,839 --> 00:07:24,719
You prepared a backup plan.

133
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:26,119
If your confession failed,

134
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:28,439
you can get away by saying that
you're friends.

135
00:07:28,719 --> 00:07:29,599
Stop it.

136
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:31,480
You don't even have confidence
in this relationship,

137
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:33,559
do you need to go on?

138
00:07:34,319 --> 00:07:35,400
Stop it.

139
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:36,999
I heard that you chose
Guanghua Vision University...

140
00:07:37,119 --> 00:07:39,279
because of Li Ming Cheng.

141
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,839
Studying fine arts needs a lot of money.

142
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,879
Your family shouldn't be able
to afford it, right?

143
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:47,159
For your own selfish desires,

144
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:50,680
you'd rather burden your parents
with the expensive tuition fees.

145
00:07:51,039 --> 00:07:53,360
Your first love hurt you and others.

146
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:54,599
Shut up.

147
00:07:54,719 --> 00:07:56,119
I earn my own money.

148
00:07:56,279 --> 00:07:58,240
I never spent any of my parents' money.

149
00:07:58,439 --> 00:08:00,559
You don't know me at all,
how could you say that about me?

150
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:02,640
So, you worked so hard...

151
00:08:03,159 --> 00:08:04,480
for Li Ming Cheng?

152
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:05,599
None of your business.

153
00:08:12,159 --> 00:08:14,039
Okay, I get it.

154
00:08:18,119 --> 00:08:19,279
Good.

155
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:21,319
Don't pester me anymore.

156
00:08:22,559 --> 00:08:24,080
Let's start by being friends.

157
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:28,200
Since you harboured a secret crush
on him since you were a teenager,

158
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,640
it's impossible for you...

159
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:30,960
to forget him immediately.

160
00:08:31,319 --> 00:08:32,359
We can take it slow.

161
00:08:32,479 --> 00:08:34,559
Did you listen to what I said?

162
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:37,040
I have to go back to the office to work.

163
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,319
Stay here, don't go anywhere.
I'll send my driver to pick you up.

164
00:08:39,439 --> 00:08:40,919
I don't need your driver to pick me up.

165
00:08:46,439 --> 00:08:47,319
This is for you.

166
00:08:47,439 --> 00:08:49,879
Let's start from zero.

167
00:08:50,119 --> 00:08:51,319
Be prepared.

168
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:56,200
I won't give up.

169
00:09:00,439 --> 00:09:02,319
Give up, scoundrel!

170
00:09:11,239 --> 00:09:12,840
Turns out in other people's eyes,

171
00:09:12,999 --> 00:09:14,720
I'm a rabbit.

172
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:17,160
No wonder I was always lied to.

173
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,960
What did you pour inside?

174
00:09:52,160 --> 00:09:54,559
Detergent, glue, sugar...

175
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:55,879
and some glycerin.

176
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:57,600
What's the use of pouring all of that?

177
00:09:57,760 --> 00:09:58,799
For fun.

178
00:10:54,319 --> 00:10:55,439
Are you feeling better now?

179
00:10:58,799 --> 00:11:00,400
So this is the way...

180
00:11:00,559 --> 00:11:02,160
to make me happy without spending money?

181
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:04,720
Okay, I'll admit it worked.

182
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:07,359
What are you talking about?

183
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:51,879
How childish.

184
00:11:51,879 --> 00:11:53,359
You played with bubbles
for the whole day.

185
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:56,119
He's the childish one, okay?
I merely went along with him.

186
00:11:56,919 --> 00:11:58,640
He saw that you were in a bad mood...

187
00:11:58,760 --> 00:11:59,999
and went to accompany you, okay?

188
00:12:00,119 --> 00:12:01,359
Or else, why would
he go to that place...

189
00:12:01,359 --> 00:12:03,119
where you were drinking to draw?

190
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:05,600
-He purposely came to look for me?
-Yes.

191
00:12:06,239 --> 00:12:08,239
You're still heartbroken,

192
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:09,600
but you tried to be strong.

193
00:12:09,799 --> 00:12:11,359
If Xiao Fei didn't realise
something was wrong,

194
00:12:11,479 --> 00:12:14,720
do you know how
dangerous it is for a girl...

195
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:15,879
to drink outside alone?

196
00:12:15,999 --> 00:12:17,720
Okay, I'll reflect upon myself.

197
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:20,999
But, he's good.

198
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,600
He's good at studying people.

199
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:24,720
That's right.

200
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,879
Are you done?

201
00:12:30,359 --> 00:12:31,479
Yes, I cleaned up.

202
00:12:51,359 --> 00:12:52,559
It's all the same.

203
00:12:52,799 --> 00:12:53,960
What are you looking at?

204
00:12:54,160 --> 00:12:55,479
Just now, you went to take a shower.

205
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:57,359
After you came out,
I went in to wash my hands.

206
00:12:57,520 --> 00:13:00,080
That time, I remembered
where everything was placed.

207
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,319
Why did you remember that?

208
00:13:01,439 --> 00:13:03,280
I didn't remember that on purpose.
Don't interrupt me.

209
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:05,520
Now, everything is
in the same position...

210
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:08,239
just like when you
finished taking a shower.

211
00:13:08,999 --> 00:13:09,919
So?

212
00:13:10,119 --> 00:13:11,239
So that means after taking a shower,

213
00:13:11,359 --> 00:13:12,799
he put everything back.

214
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:15,200
That's nothing.
Maybe he didn't use anything.

215
00:13:17,679 --> 00:13:19,520
Did you mop the floor after showering?

216
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:20,439
No.

217
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:23,200
The mop was used.

218
00:13:25,799 --> 00:13:26,479
This is too much.

219
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:28,239
He didn't dry the mop after using it.

220
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:34,479
This is where the contradiction lies.

221
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:36,520
He isn't good at doing that,

222
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:38,679
but he purposely cleaned everything.

223
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:41,319
He was afraid that his presence...

224
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:42,960
will cause trouble to others.

225
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:45,359
Don't you think he's
living too cautiously?

226
00:13:46,119 --> 00:13:47,239
Is he...

227
00:13:47,359 --> 00:13:48,479
a fugitive...

228
00:13:48,679 --> 00:13:50,119
that is afraid of being discovered?

229
00:13:50,280 --> 00:13:51,520
Did you go crazy because
you watched too many dramas?

230
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:52,400
Then, tell me.

231
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:53,840
Is he being cautious...

232
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:55,160
because he isn't used
to living with others?

233
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:57,160
No, I think it's exactly the opposite.

234
00:13:58,239 --> 00:14:01,400
Living in someone else's house
may be normal to him.

235
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:06,200
I'm curious.

236
00:14:06,919 --> 00:14:09,200
He's just a kid, there's nothing
mysterious about him.

237
00:14:10,280 --> 00:14:11,919
He's not just a normal kid.

238
00:14:12,119 --> 00:14:14,960
He's a wealthy kid.

239
00:14:16,119 --> 00:14:17,080
What do you mean?

240
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:19,999
Let's talk in my room.

241
00:14:20,239 --> 00:14:21,520
Let's go...

242
00:14:35,919 --> 00:14:37,960
Isn't this Ning Fei's card?

243
00:14:38,119 --> 00:14:39,760
He asked for my help last time.

244
00:14:39,919 --> 00:14:42,319
He said he forgot the password and
asked me to crack his PIN number.

245
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:43,840
I asked him for some hints.

246
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:44,999
Now, I successfully...

247
00:14:45,119 --> 00:14:46,319
cracked the password.

248
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:48,239
Guess how much money is in this account.

249
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:49,359
How much money?

250
00:14:55,319 --> 00:14:56,479
You're lying, right?

251
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:58,999
How could he...

252
00:14:59,479 --> 00:15:00,999
Did you confirm it?

253
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:03,160
Did he take his benefactor's card?

254
00:15:03,479 --> 00:15:05,400
I confirmed it.
This is his personal account.

255
00:15:05,559 --> 00:15:07,799
Moreover, all transfers are normal.

256
00:15:07,999 --> 00:15:10,600
Money was only transferred in.
Looks legit to me.

257
00:15:10,879 --> 00:15:11,760
That's right.

258
00:15:11,919 --> 00:15:13,960
His dad is a pottery master, right?

259
00:15:14,119 --> 00:15:15,760
The price of the bowl
he made is expensive.

260
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:17,760
Do the money belongs to his dad?

261
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:19,559
I checked on his dad too.

262
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:22,200
His dad is the Van Gogh of China.

263
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:24,080
When he was alive, he was destitute.

264
00:15:24,239 --> 00:15:26,160
After he died, he was not famous too.

265
00:15:26,319 --> 00:15:27,479
A few decades after he died,

266
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,799
his work was discovered.

267
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:31,439
And, guess who owns all of his work?

268
00:15:31,559 --> 00:15:33,640
-Who is it?
-Yun Ma Art.

269
00:15:35,559 --> 00:15:36,960
The benefactor.

270
00:15:38,239 --> 00:15:40,919
The Ning family and
Wei family are close friends.

271
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:43,280
So, Madam He treated him well.

272
00:15:43,439 --> 00:15:46,760
From now on, stop calling him toy boy.
It's a bad nickname.

273
00:15:46,960 --> 00:15:48,799
Xiao Fei is...

274
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:51,080
really wealthy.

275
00:15:52,760 --> 00:15:54,479
Oh dear.

276
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:58,160
We asked a wealthy man to
sleep in our living room.

277
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,239
Oh dear.

278
00:16:12,999 --> 00:16:13,919
What's wrong with her?

279
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,200
She's digesting.

280
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:17,200
Digesting what?

281
00:16:17,439 --> 00:16:19,640
Search high and low to find nothing...

282
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:21,840
when that person is
staying in the same home.

283
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:23,960
She needs to digest that.

284
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:25,479
I don't get you.

285
00:16:25,679 --> 00:16:26,799
By the way, did you see...

286
00:16:26,799 --> 00:16:28,160
a blue wallet?

287
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:29,879
No. Did you lose it?

288
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:33,400
No.

289
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:35,319
I probably left it in my room.

290
00:16:35,520 --> 00:16:36,559
I'll go and look for it again.

291
00:17:07,599 --> 00:17:08,839
It isn't in my bag.

292
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:10,800
It isn't in my drawer.

293
00:17:11,040 --> 00:17:13,959
Living room, bedroom, I searched
the whole house but couldn't find it.

294
00:17:14,239 --> 00:17:16,400
Where did I leave my wallet?

295
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:19,479
My living expenses for this month.

296
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:21,160
No.

297
00:17:21,359 --> 00:17:23,239
Recall where you went today.

298
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:24,800
There must be a clue.

299
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:38,680
Right.

300
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:40,999
I dropped it then.

301
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:42,359
Oh no...

302
00:17:42,359 --> 00:17:44,440
It must be taken by someone.

303
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:47,599
My living expenses.

304
00:17:47,959 --> 00:17:50,520
Heavens, it's fine if you hurt me.

305
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:53,400
Why did you hurt my wallet?

306
00:18:04,999 --> 00:18:06,760
Zhou Shi, we're having lunch.

307
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:08,520
You're being too
environmentally friendly.

308
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:10,440
I'm on a diet.

309
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:11,879
I thought only Lin Fei Fei...

310
00:18:11,879 --> 00:18:13,400
will do something like that.

311
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:17,040
What did you say?

312
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:20,520
I never thought...

313
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:22,640
I'd see you eat fast food in my life.

314
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,719
Won't you regret eating it?

315
00:18:24,879 --> 00:18:25,800
The calories are high.

316
00:18:25,959 --> 00:18:27,359
These aren't mine.

317
00:18:30,479 --> 00:18:32,040
Ning Fei, here.

318
00:18:33,359 --> 00:18:35,359
She took action.

319
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:37,239
Don't nag. Help me if you're my friend.

320
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:38,719
Sister Zhou Shi.

321
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:42,320
Why are you eating so little food?

322
00:18:44,079 --> 00:18:45,959
Women need to go on diets.

323
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:47,760
Zhou Shi finally realised it.

324
00:18:47,959 --> 00:18:49,560
Yes...

325
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,560
By the way, you like to eat
fried chicken, right?

326
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:53,040
I bought an extra set.

327
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:03,680
Eat more.

328
00:19:04,079 --> 00:19:06,040
Eat what others give you.

329
00:19:14,879 --> 00:19:16,359
Why is Fei Fei suddenly...

330
00:19:16,599 --> 00:19:17,520
Since she realised...

331
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:20,479
there's a oyster beside her.

332
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:22,560
What nonsense are you talking about?

333
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:23,839
Is it delicious?

334
00:19:29,119 --> 00:19:29,959
You want to add me?

335
00:19:30,119 --> 00:19:32,680
Come out with a question I can't answer.

336
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:41,479
90 seconds.

337
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,119
She didn't blacklist me.

338
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:55,959
That means I can go on?

339
00:20:00,359 --> 00:20:03,800
Why does it feel like
a full blown competition now?

340
00:20:04,599 --> 00:20:06,800
Is there any question
that she doesn't know?

341
00:20:15,199 --> 00:20:16,640
I'll ask Shi Shi next time.

342
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:21,479
Zhou Shi.

343
00:20:21,879 --> 00:20:23,640
You ate so little food.
You need to work at night.

344
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:25,119
Can your body handle it?

345
00:20:25,999 --> 00:20:27,400
Of course.

346
00:20:35,359 --> 00:20:37,320
I can't stand this anymore.

347
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:46,959
What a waste.

348
00:20:47,760 --> 00:20:48,959
Don't they know that
there are many people...

349
00:20:48,959 --> 00:20:51,119
who don't get to eat in this world?

350
00:20:55,280 --> 00:20:56,959
For example, me.

351
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:02,599
These need to be thrown away...

352
00:21:02,839 --> 00:21:03,920
into the dustbin.

353
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:05,599
They are going to be thrown away anyway.

354
00:21:23,119 --> 00:21:24,119
What are you doing?

355
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:27,239
Nothing...

356
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:29,800
You don't have to clean this up.

357
00:21:30,119 --> 00:21:32,079
There are VIP guests coming soon.

358
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,520
Quick, prepare the drinks.

359
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:34,400
Yes.

360
00:21:37,079 --> 00:21:38,079
Director Sheng.

361
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:40,680
I want to ask...

362
00:21:41,160 --> 00:21:43,520
about my salary this month.

363
00:21:43,879 --> 00:21:44,920
Salary?

364
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:46,479
The accounting manager is not in.

365
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:48,839
It'll probably be
delayed until next week.

366
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:51,079
What's wrong? Do you need money?

367
00:21:51,239 --> 00:21:52,959
No, as long as you can give it.

368
00:21:53,119 --> 00:21:54,040
Hurry up and go.

369
00:22:02,839 --> 00:22:04,320
Chairman Wei, I'm sorry.

370
00:22:04,479 --> 00:22:06,520
Sorry to keep you waiting.
The room will be ready soon.

371
00:22:06,719 --> 00:22:08,879
It's fine. I can wait for a while.

372
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:11,199
At least I saw something interesting.

373
00:22:26,839 --> 00:22:28,040
Who?

374
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:37,879
Hello, Miss Zhou Shi.
This is your parcel.

375
00:22:38,040 --> 00:22:39,560
What are these?

376
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:43,440
What else? Presents.

377
00:22:44,599 --> 00:22:45,999
Wei Qing again.

378
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,680
Who else?

379
00:22:47,879 --> 00:22:49,359
Previously, you sent off a batch.

380
00:22:49,479 --> 00:22:51,119
Now, another batch is here.

381
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:54,400
Why don't you ask the deliveryman
to take them back?

382
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:56,599
I don't have money to do so.

383
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:02,560
When will he stop?

384
00:23:11,760 --> 00:23:14,680
As expected, there's a reason why...

385
00:23:14,999 --> 00:23:16,359
he became the new favourite
of the art world.

386
00:23:19,560 --> 00:23:20,959
Hand these to the company's designer.

387
00:23:21,119 --> 00:23:22,320
Ask them to use the designs...

388
00:23:22,440 --> 00:23:24,160
for our new collection.

389
00:23:24,359 --> 00:23:26,680
Then, use Xun Ran's exhibition
as a marketing tool.

390
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:27,760
Okay.

391
00:23:32,360 --> 00:23:34,634
[Zhou Shi]

392
00:23:41,640 --> 00:23:42,560
When will you stop?

393
00:23:42,680 --> 00:23:44,280
When are you going to stop pestering me?

394
00:23:44,440 --> 00:23:45,760
Why are you speaking so loudly?

395
00:23:45,879 --> 00:23:47,479
Can you not be so rude?

396
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:48,879
Stop the nonsense.

397
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:50,440
When are you going to stop
sending me things?

398
00:23:50,560 --> 00:23:52,440
The parcels have reached?
That's fast.

399
00:23:52,560 --> 00:23:53,839
I'll give the shop a good rating.

400
00:23:54,479 --> 00:23:55,839
Am I joking?

401
00:23:55,999 --> 00:23:56,839
That day when you gave me flowers,

402
00:23:56,839 --> 00:23:58,239
didn't I say clearly...

403
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,999
not to send me anything?

404
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:02,640
You're wasting money
for the delivery fee.

405
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:06,239
I can't hear you clearly.

406
00:24:09,760 --> 00:24:10,719
I can't hear you.

407
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:12,199
The signal is bad here.

408
00:24:12,359 --> 00:24:14,560
Tell me in person.

409
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:16,040
I'll send you the address.

410
00:24:16,239 --> 00:24:17,959
Come here if you want to see me.

411
00:24:27,479 --> 00:24:28,959
That far?

412
00:24:38,320 --> 00:24:40,839
I don't even have money
to buy a screen protector.

413
00:24:41,160 --> 00:24:43,560
Who gave you the courage
to throw your phone?

414
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:45,440
Heavens!

415
00:24:46,839 --> 00:24:48,479
I was wrong.

416
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:51,800
Please help me to punish Wei Qing!

417
00:24:51,959 --> 00:24:54,640
We aren't compatible.

418
00:25:06,199 --> 00:25:07,160
This way, please.

419
00:25:10,800 --> 00:25:12,839
You're here? That's fast.

420
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:14,760
I spend a lot of money
to take a taxi here.

421
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:15,839
Of course I'm fast.

422
00:25:15,999 --> 00:25:18,359
You're sincere.
Here, take a sip of tea.

423
00:25:24,359 --> 00:25:25,400
It's delicious.

424
00:25:25,959 --> 00:25:26,920
I'm thirsty.

425
00:25:27,079 --> 00:25:28,239
I knew you'd be thirsty when you come.

426
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:29,999
So, I added honey and mint.

427
00:25:30,160 --> 00:25:31,119
Thank you.

428
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:39,479
Actually, I'm here to say...

429
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:50,119
It's tea time now.

430
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:52,599
Let's eat before we talk.

431
00:25:57,719 --> 00:26:00,320
Can I eat them?

432
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:01,920
Of course.

433
00:26:08,320 --> 00:26:09,479
Don't do this.

434
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:10,920
Don't think that
you can make me yield...

435
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:11,999
by giving me a sugar-coated bullet.

436
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:13,760
Let me tell you, impossible.

437
00:26:13,959 --> 00:26:15,879
I hate to be lied to.

438
00:26:16,079 --> 00:26:17,520
Don't think that by spending money
to make people happy,

439
00:26:17,520 --> 00:26:18,719
they will forgive you.

440
00:26:18,879 --> 00:26:20,640
Let me tell you.
Maybe it works for others,

441
00:26:20,760 --> 00:26:22,320
but it won't work for me.

442
00:26:22,999 --> 00:26:24,079
What do I have to do...

443
00:26:24,239 --> 00:26:25,640
to forgive me?

444
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,119
Apologise to me.

445
00:26:27,839 --> 00:26:28,640
Impossible.

446
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:30,479
Then there's nothing else to say.

447
00:26:31,079 --> 00:26:33,359
You'd better find someone
to take away all the things.

448
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:34,239
Or else,

449
00:26:34,359 --> 00:26:36,199
wait until I have money
to send them back.

450
00:26:38,959 --> 00:26:39,879
Goodbye.

451
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:49,479
Don't blame me.

452
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:51,119
It's not that I don't want to eat you,

453
00:26:51,359 --> 00:26:53,359
but I can't eat you.

454
00:26:53,760 --> 00:26:54,959
Heavens,

455
00:26:55,119 --> 00:26:57,239
why are you torturing me?

456
00:26:57,760 --> 00:26:58,520
No.

457
00:26:58,719 --> 00:27:00,760
Zhou Shi, you did the right thing.

458
00:27:01,839 --> 00:27:03,560
You can't fall into his trap.

459
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:08,160
It's not like I haven't seen
good food before.

460
00:27:13,879 --> 00:27:15,040
Take them away.

461
00:27:21,359 --> 00:27:22,599
So troublesome.

462
00:27:22,959 --> 00:27:24,879
I didn't expect for her
to be so stubborn.

463
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:26,680
Actually,

464
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:30,320
I think Miss Zhou...

465
00:27:31,320 --> 00:27:32,320
is different from others.

466
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:33,920
What's the use of
being different from others?

467
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:36,839
Nobody has ever rejected me like that.

468
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:37,839
If it wasn't because of my body...

469
00:27:37,920 --> 00:27:39,999
didn't have a adverse reaction
towards her,

470
00:27:40,199 --> 00:27:42,520
will I waste that much time for her?

471
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:47,239
Actually, it isn't hard...

472
00:27:47,879 --> 00:27:48,959
to make her accept you.

473
00:27:50,800 --> 00:27:51,760
What do you mean?

474
00:27:52,520 --> 00:27:53,400
Apologise.

475
00:27:53,560 --> 00:27:54,560
Impossible.

476
00:27:54,719 --> 00:27:57,199
I've never apologise to anyone.

477
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:59,599
If you don't apologise,

478
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:01,999
she probably won't forgive you
for the rest of her life.

479
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:04,520
Think about it.

480
00:28:04,920 --> 00:28:06,920
After 10 years,

481
00:28:07,119 --> 00:28:09,640
you finally found someone like her.

482
00:28:09,839 --> 00:28:12,520
Are you going to lose
because of an apology?

483
00:28:13,479 --> 00:28:14,400
But...

484
00:28:15,599 --> 00:28:16,760
But, I don't know how to apologise.

485
00:28:16,959 --> 00:28:20,359
It's just three words.
It isn't that hard.

486
00:28:21,479 --> 00:28:23,079
If you go after her now,

487
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:25,119
you may be able to catch her.

488
00:28:35,479 --> 00:28:37,079
It's all Wei Qing's fault.

489
00:28:37,239 --> 00:28:38,800
He chose a remote place.

490
00:28:39,199 --> 00:28:40,920
There isn't a single bus here.

491
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:43,400
I have to walk back myself.

492
00:28:57,280 --> 00:28:59,160
-Let me send you back.
-No need.

493
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:00,280
It's hard to get a taxi here.

494
00:29:00,400 --> 00:29:01,680
Who said I'm going to get a taxi?

495
00:29:01,839 --> 00:29:03,079
The scenery is beautiful here.

496
00:29:03,239 --> 00:29:04,760
Can't I take a walk?

497
00:29:08,239 --> 00:29:09,320
I'm sorry.

498
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:14,599
What did you say?

499
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:18,920
Are you going to say it or not?

500
00:29:19,079 --> 00:29:20,440
If you won't say it, I'll leave.

501
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:22,440
I'm sorry.

502
00:29:24,359 --> 00:29:25,879
You're apologising to me?

503
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:31,599
You're apologising, how rare.

504
00:29:31,959 --> 00:29:34,680
Do you think I want to do so?
It it wasn't because...

505
00:29:34,839 --> 00:29:35,959
If it wasn't because of what?

506
00:29:36,119 --> 00:29:38,599
Anyway, I apologised.

507
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:40,359
We're even now.

508
00:29:41,479 --> 00:29:43,520
You seem unwilling.

509
00:29:43,719 --> 00:29:45,199
I don't think you're sincere.

510
00:29:45,359 --> 00:29:46,320
You...

511
00:29:47,520 --> 00:29:48,359
Okay.

512
00:29:48,479 --> 00:29:50,160
Let's move on.

513
00:29:51,239 --> 00:29:52,239
Get in the car.

514
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:54,560
Are you getting in the car or not?

515
00:29:54,719 --> 00:29:55,920
It's hard to get a taxi here.

516
00:29:56,239 --> 00:29:57,160
If you're willing to walk,

517
00:29:57,160 --> 00:29:58,040
I won't stop you.

518
00:29:58,160 --> 00:29:59,199
I'll get in...

519
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:07,320
You look like you're suffering.
Be happy.

520
00:30:09,999 --> 00:30:11,479
Let's go, Master Wei.

521
00:30:22,199 --> 00:30:23,239
Here is the bus station.

522
00:30:23,959 --> 00:30:24,879
Thank you.

523
00:30:31,320 --> 00:30:32,079
By the way,

524
00:30:32,239 --> 00:30:34,440
find someone to take the parcels away.

525
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:36,320
My wallet is empty now.

526
00:30:36,479 --> 00:30:37,839
I won't send them back.

527
00:30:38,839 --> 00:30:40,599
Did you see the contents of the parcel?

528
00:30:40,920 --> 00:30:42,239
Clothes, accessories and bags.

529
00:30:42,359 --> 00:30:44,440
What else?

530
00:30:44,640 --> 00:30:45,839
Look at the contents of the parcels.

531
00:30:45,999 --> 00:30:47,359
If you don't like them,

532
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:48,760
I'll ask someone to pick them up.

533
00:30:51,999 --> 00:30:53,959
He is acting strangely.

534
00:30:54,800 --> 00:30:55,920
Did he set a trap for me again?

535
00:30:56,079 --> 00:31:00,359
♪ Was "you" as stated by her ♪

536
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:03,199
♪ The "us" that I yearn of ♪

537
00:31:03,320 --> 00:31:07,879
♪ I was the only serious one ♪

538
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:10,640
♪ The "us" that I yearn of ♪

539
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:17,400
♪ If you didn't tell me firmly... ♪

540
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:19,320
What is he doing?

541
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:21,680
There are enough food
to last me for a month.

542
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:46,879
I received what you sent me.

543
00:31:47,239 --> 00:31:48,400
Are you satisfied?

544
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:50,800
This time, they aren't expensive trash.

545
00:31:51,440 --> 00:31:53,359
They are life saving to me.

546
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:54,599
Thank you.

547
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:55,839
This is the first time.

548
00:31:55,999 --> 00:31:56,920
What?

549
00:31:57,119 --> 00:31:59,640
The first time you're thanking me
for my presents.

550
00:32:00,280 --> 00:32:01,959
The point of giving out presents
isn't to show off your wealth.

551
00:32:02,119 --> 00:32:03,760
Presents don't have to be expensive.

